{"name": "jawadb", "metadata": {"name": "jawadb", "version": "0.1.2", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 3 - Alpha", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9"], "home_page": null, "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "A simple persistent JSON database for Python", "upload_time": 1734978095}, "documentation": ["# JawaDB\n\nA simple persistent JSON database for Python that acts like a regular dictionary or list.\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\npip install jawadb\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n```python\nimport jawadb\n\n# Use as dictionary\ndb = jawadb.load(\"mydata.json\")\ndb[\"key\"] = \"value\"\ndb[\"nested\"] = {\"foo\": \"bar\"}\n# File is automatically saved when db is garbage collected\n\n# Use as list\ndb = jawadb.load(\"mylist.json\")\ndb += [\"item1\", \"item2\"]\ndb.append(\"item3\")\n# File is automatically saved\n```\n\n## Features\n\n- Automatic persistence to JSON file\n- Use as either dictionary or list (type is determined by first operation)\n- Handles nested structures\n- Atomic file writes\n- Saves on program exit, Ctrl-C, and garbage collection\n- Type hints included\n\n## License\n\nMIT License"], "modules": [{"name": "jawadb", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "jawadb._save_db", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "db_ref", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Save a database using its weak reference."]}, {"name": "jawadb._save_all_dbs", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Save all active databases during interpreter shutdown."]}, {"name": "jawadb._signal_handler", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "signum", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name"